name: Air Fryer Venison Burgers
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: This is a fast and easy way to prepare venison burgers when you don't feel like firing up the grill.
directions: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions
Combine venison, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt, onion powder, and ground pepper in a large bowl
Mix with your hands until evenly combined
Place 2 patties in the basket of the air fryer and cook for 6 minutes
Carefully flip the patties and cook for 2 minutes more
Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate and repeat with remaining patties
Serve on hamburger buns with your favorite condiments and toppings
